## Project Context

- **Client:** Chick-fil-A College Football Hall of Fame (cfbhall.com)
- **Agency work:** Client-shareable **search prototype** for presentation + Figma import later
- **This repo:** Static prototype — **NOT** production Umbraco
- **CMS target (later):** Umbraco Search / Examine index — **NO Search & Filter Pro**

---

## What We Are Building

1. Global header search — default **icon** → expand to input (desktop + mobile)
2. Predictive dropdown — HOF (avatar + team badge) vs general (text/icon)
3. `/search` page — query hero, category filters, result cards, empty state
4. Mock Umbraco backend — local `search-index.json` (Examine-shaped documents)

Primary user intents: **inductees**, **tickets**, **events**.

---

## Tech Stack (do not change without asking)

- Prefer **vanilla HTML / CSS / JS** (matches prior CloudMellow prototypes; easy client share + Figma capture)
- Optional light Vite static shell later if needed — ask first
- **No** React/Next unless Matt explicitly switches
- **No** Search & Filter Pro or other paid search plugins
- Fonts: athletic condensed uppercase for headings + geometric sans for body — **not Inter / Roboto / Arial / system default stack as the brand face**
- Brand colors live in a tokens file once created — never hardcode crimson/navy outside tokens

### Planned brand tokens (from CFHF design spec)

| Token role | Direction |
|---|---|
| Primary accent | Deep athletic red / crimson (TICKETS CTAs, accents) |
| Secondary | Dark navy (header, logo ground, footer) |
| Surfaces | White / light gray |
| Overlays | Charcoal / midnight |
| Avoid | Gold/indigo “generic SaaS” look from the early draft HTML; purple gradients; cream+serif terracotta |

---

## Umbraco Mimic (required pattern)

One shared dataset for typeahead **and** results:

```text
data/search-index.json  →  fields shaped like Examine hits
```

Document shape (keep realistic):

- `id`, `docType`, `category`, `title`, `excerpt`, `url`, `image`, `date`
- Inductees also: `inductionYear`, `team`, `teamBadge`

Categories (until Matt confirms otherwise — match the brief):

- `all` | `inductees` | `news` | `events` | `general-tickets`

Filter UI must actually filter this data. Do not ship toy toggles that only change CSS `display` without filtering.

---

## Build Order (follow this)

1. Brand tokens + base shell
2. Global header search states
3. Predictive dropdown (same data source)
4. Search page hero + layout
5. Category filters (desktop sticky + mobile pills) — real filtering
6. Standard + Hall of Famer cards
7. Empty state
8. A11y + mobile polish + share link (GitHub Pages later if asked)

---

## What NOT To Do

- Do not rebuild the full CFHF marketing site
- Do not add Search & Filter Pro or Umbraco packages
- Do not invent final legal logo lockups — placeholder wordmark OK
- Do not leave Inter + amber/gold as the client-facing brand
- Do not commit secrets or real private API keys (none needed)
- Do not force-push `master` or skip hooks
- Do not guess blocked layout decisions (sidebar side, category merge) — ask or use the defaults noted above and flag in JOURNAL

